"The vote will take place before the end of February 2013," Nacher said.
Controversial EU regulations include, for example, the obligation to add organic components to fuels, which has harmful consequences for the environment, or the ban on the use of reliable mercury thermometers, simply because they contain a relatively small quantity of a dangerous substance, or the chicken cage size directive, which has led to the increase in prices.
