At the moment, this judgment is not respected.
This is a problem between a South American country and a Central American country.
Conflicts are inevitable, but they must be overcome by the will to move forward together.
We must resolve them as a whole to overcome them and move forward.
At the same time, he expressed confidence in the successful resolution of the maritime border dispute between Peru and Chile in the same court and affirmed that it is "beneficial for Latin America to bring the matter before international bodies if the two countries agree to accept a judgment as firm as it is".
Referring to the possibility of his presentation as a candidate in the future presidential elections in Ecuador, with a view to running for a third consecutive term, he said he saw this possibility "with a lot of optimism and joy, although it is sometimes quite difficult".
Correa said that if he lost the February 2013 primary, he would withdraw from public life.
On a personal level, power has never interested me, but in situations as unjust as those of Ecuador, this socio-economic poverty can only be resolved through political power.
